        'You can never have too many main course recipes, so give Mushroom Goat Cheese Baked Eggs a try. One serving contains <b>706 calories</b>, <b>40g of protein</b>, and <b>25g of fat</b>. This lacto ovo vegetarian recipe serves 2 and costs <b>$4.53 per serving</b>. This recipe from fullbellysisters.blogspot.com has 135 fans. A mixture of ghee, eggs, shallots, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly <b>45 minutes</b>. With a spoonacular <b>score of 94%</b>, this dish is outstanding. Similar recipes are <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/mushroom-goat-cheese-baked-eggs-1625563">Mushroom Goat Cheese Baked Eggs</a>, <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/mushroom-spinach-and-goat-cheese-baked-eggs-625772">Mushroom Spinach and Goat Cheese Baked Eggs</a>, and <a href="https://spoonacular.com/recipes/easy-mushroom-and-goats-cheese-scrambled-eggs-1323721">Easy mushroom and goat\'s cheese scrambled eggs</a>.',
